1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:36,620
The Six Vegapunks

3
00:01:37,290 --> 00:01:41,460
You can run, but you can't hide!

4
00:01:45,290 --> 00:01:47,630
Hakugan, take charge of the Polar Tang!

5
00:01:47,630 --> 00:01:48,670
Okay!

6
00:01:49,340 --> 00:01:51,010
Shachi! Penguin!

7
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:52,050
Into the sea!

8
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:53,510
You got it!

9
00:01:59,270 --> 00:02:01,100
Re-Room!

10
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,860
What's this?

11
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:17,530
Amputate!

12
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:32,300
That's not what I heard it could do!

13
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:34,130
Is it an awakened technique?!

14
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:36,680
Alright! Fall!

15
00:02:38,850 --> 00:02:40,060
Not yet!

16
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:45,230
You son of a bitch!

17
00:02:45,230 --> 00:02:48,020
Quake Crush!

18
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,350
Damn that monster!

19
00:03:33,690 --> 00:03:35,610
My goodness!

20
00:03:35,610 --> 00:03:38,610
Stronger, are you dead?

21
00:03:38,610 --> 00:03:40,240
I see...

22
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,830
You were a good boy.

23
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:46,870
Eat this!

24
00:03:53,090 --> 00:03:54,420
What are those?!

25
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:56,800
Get away!

26
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,340
Apple bombs!

27
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:21,660
Huh?

28
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:25,580
Don't mess with guys from
the North Blue's frozen ports!

29
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:28,330
You don't stand a chance against us at sea!

30
00:04:28,330 --> 00:04:30,460
Your ship's as good as sunk!

31
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:36,300
Prepare to attack!

32
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,670
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

33
00:04:55,650 --> 00:04:57,740
Jean Bart! Three o'clock!

34
00:04:57,740 --> 00:04:59,400
A sniper!

35
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:01,410
Protect the captain!

36
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:03,160
I'm on it!

37
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,330
Oops...

38
00:05:13,290 --> 00:05:15,750
His defense is strong.

39
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:18,920
K-Room!

40
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:33,650
That doesn't even tickle!

41
00:05:33,650 --> 00:05:35,610
Shock Wille!

42
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:50,580
See, that's what happens
when you charge in recklessly...

43
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:51,750
Warp.

44
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:56,920
Commodore, shall we return to the ship?

45
00:05:56,920 --> 00:06:00,210
Don't be stupid!
We finish what we start.

46
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,090
Understood.

47
00:06:03,090 --> 00:06:04,550
Warp.

48
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:18,110
Blackbeard is here!

49
00:06:18,110 --> 00:06:20,740
Are all your officers devil fruit users?

50
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:27,870
That just means they're all weak to the sea!

51
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:33,830
The perks of devil fruits
are well worth the drawbacks!

52
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:35,460
Room!

53
00:06:39,590 --> 00:06:40,670
Takt!

54
00:06:47,930 --> 00:06:49,810
K-Room!

55
00:06:54,770 --> 00:06:56,900
They're attacking from below!

56
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:59,150
They're tryin' to sink us!

57
00:06:59,150 --> 00:07:02,360
How can they be this good in the water?!

58
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:16,210
Look out!

59
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:24,510
We're just getting attacked a little.
It'll stop shaking soon.

60
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:27,840
Because our commodore is the strongest!

61
00:07:28,970 --> 00:07:30,550
If Mama's still alive...

62
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:34,270
you won't be talking like that for long.

63
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:36,980
Charlotte Pudding

64
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:36,980
Big Mom Pirates

65
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:43,480
The guy we're fighting right now
is the one who killed her!

66
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:48,160
Times ain't gonna change if
the old legends are still ruling the roost!

67
00:07:49,030 --> 00:07:51,660
On Cacao Island, 
in the Whole Cake Island archipelago,

68
00:07:51,660 --> 00:07:56,370
two intruders have come to
Pudding's home, Chocolat Town.

69
00:08:19,690 --> 00:08:22,730
Their goal was to abduct Pudding.

70
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:26,820
Those intruders were...

71
00:08:26,820 --> 00:08:29,950
the Blackbeard Pirates' Van Augur...

72
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:31,030
and...

73
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,490
Kuzan.

74
00:08:35,290 --> 00:08:40,040
I know what you people
are trying to make me do.

75
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:43,340
I won't let that happen.

76
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:56,470
Black Vortex!

77
00:08:58,230 --> 00:09:02,860
Emperor Blackbeard and Trafalgar Law
just clashed at Winner Island in the New World!

78
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:05,360
Once again, I have to wait
and see what happens.

79
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:09,740
Being fleet admiral is frustrating...

80
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:13,700
Future Island, Egghead

81
00:09:18,790 --> 00:09:22,500
The pacifista stopped all of a sudden.

82
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,880
Now, Bonney...

83
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:29,470
Luffy, 70 Years Old

84
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:29,470
(In One Possible Future)

85
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:29,470
you could have disguised me as a better age...

86
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:35,550
Look, I get how you feel, but...

87
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:40,680
if you won't even let us beat up the ones
that aren't actually your dad, we'll be–

88
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:42,770
Be nice, Luffy!

89
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,400
Sorry, Bonney.

90
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:50,360
We've just been through a lot
with those pacifista, is all.

91
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:57,450
Also... turn me back to how I was, please...

92
00:09:59,830 --> 00:10:01,790
Oh, boy...

93
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:05,460
Since they're clones of someone
who was originally a human,

94
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:07,880
it stands to reason that he'd have a family.

95
00:10:08,710 --> 00:10:11,090
Don't take this the wrong way, Bonney.

96
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:17,560
To my knowledge, Kuma was once
the wicked king of Sorbet.

97
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:20,140
He became a pirate after
his people drove him out.

98
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:22,810
Then, after joining the Revolutionary Army,

99
00:10:22,810 --> 00:10:26,650
the Marines arrested him
and gave him a life sentence.

100
00:10:27,230 --> 00:10:33,070
But due to Vegapunk's fascination
with his physique and potential,

101
00:10:33,070 --> 00:10:37,160
he was allowed to return to sea
as one of the Seven Warlords...

102
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:41,580
on the condition that he submits himself
to body augmentation and cloning.

103
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,540
Is that right?

104
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:48,880
The Warlord and cloning stuff I get.

105
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:50,210
But being made a cyborg?!

106
00:10:50,210 --> 00:10:52,130
It's basically a death sentence!

107
00:10:52,130 --> 00:10:55,010
No one would accept it
if they knew what it meant!

108
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:57,600
You're right...

109
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,260
Still, that's a lot of conditions
for a life sentence.

110
00:11:00,850 --> 00:11:03,890
Just how awful were the crimes
Kuma the Tyrant committed...?

111
00:11:08,810 --> 00:11:10,980
My father was not a tyrant!

112
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:13,240
He hated the World Government!

113
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:15,070
He would never work with them!

114
00:11:15,070 --> 00:11:17,200
They must've modified him by force!

115
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,490
Hey, are you trying to kill us?!

116
00:11:19,490 --> 00:11:21,370
That was way too close!

117
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:24,000
By the way, was that...

118
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,120
A beam saber?!

119
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,710
Awesome!

120
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:30,590
This is a scrap heap...

121
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:32,840
It must be full of Vegapunk's junk.

122
00:11:33,340 --> 00:11:34,590
I can use this...

123
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:39,140
Anyway, this is murder in the name of science!

124
00:11:52,230 --> 00:11:56,150
My father said his people are special.

125
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:58,530
But so what?!

126
00:11:58,530 --> 00:12:00,990
That doesn't give them
the right to experiment on him!

127
00:12:01,370 --> 00:12:03,700
That doesn't give them the right to kill him!

128
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,200
You said it!

129
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:06,910
A special people?

130
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:09,880
Bonney...

131
00:12:11,210 --> 00:12:13,550
Could you turn me back, too?

132
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:21,680
We're flying!

133
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:23,930
Team Sunny

134
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:23,930
The robot is actually flying!

135
00:12:23,930 --> 00:12:25,930
Cool!

136
00:12:27,140 --> 00:12:31,110
This here Vegaforce-01 is propelled
by the jets on its back,

137
00:12:31,110 --> 00:12:33,070
and floats with an anti-gravity unit.

138
00:12:33,070 --> 00:12:34,900
"Anti-gravity"?!

139
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:39,530
The island A.C. system makes this possible,
but someday it might be all over the globe!

140
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,580
Whoa! Check out this city!

141
00:12:44,450 --> 00:12:47,370
I've never seen buildings like these.

142
00:12:47,370 --> 00:12:48,830
Let's climb higher!

143
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:59,010
Look, a monster!

144
00:12:59,010 --> 00:13:00,470
Cool!

145
00:13:00,470 --> 00:13:02,390
And a giant robot?!

146
00:13:02,390 --> 00:13:04,180
How many are there?!

147
00:13:04,180 --> 00:13:05,930
Those fish are flying!

148
00:13:05,930 --> 00:13:08,640
Is it because of the anti-gravity device?

149
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,350
What a futuristic city!

150
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:11,690
Darn tootin'!

151
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:14,320
On this island, the future is now!

152
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:19,780
This is Future Island, Egghead!

153
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:25,700
Above the clouds is
the laboratory level, the Labophase!

154
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:28,620
And down below is
the factory level, the Fabriophase!

155
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:31,330
The workers and researchers live there.

156
00:13:31,330 --> 00:13:34,790
I hear your captain is down 
there causing a hullabaloo.

157
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:37,170
Good to know he's okay.

158
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:46,680
Here we are!

159
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:49,680
Labophase
Future Island, Egghead

160
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:49,680
I can hardly wait!

161
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:53,520
Hey Zoro, aren't you coming?!
And you, Brook?!

162
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:54,900
I'll watch the ship.

163
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:55,730
Me, too.

164
00:13:55,730 --> 00:13:58,650
I don't trust that woman.

165
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:02,070
Man, this jackass...

166
00:14:02,070 --> 00:14:06,200
Oh, Lilith! Just ignore that Moss Head nobody!

167
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,240
What is it?

168
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,750
Try it.

169
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:11,960
Try what?

170
00:14:15,210 --> 00:14:16,590
It's like the sky island!

171
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:17,290
Right?!

172
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:18,300
Really?!

173
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:20,130
What the heck?!

174
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:23,090
So cool!

175
00:14:23,090 --> 00:14:24,840
This is so nostalgic!

176
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,100
Oh, really?

177
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:27,470
First time for me!

178
00:14:27,470 --> 00:14:29,100
What the heck is this?!

179
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:30,810
Did Vegapunk make this too?!

180
00:14:31,310 --> 00:14:33,270
Yep! You're spot on!

181
00:14:33,770 --> 00:14:37,150
By precisely conditioning the island's air,

182
00:14:37,150 --> 00:14:41,190
I modified the density of pyrobroin
and moisture in the condensation nuclei,

183
00:14:41,190 --> 00:14:44,610
recreating the island clouds
and sea clouds of the sky islands!

184
00:14:44,610 --> 00:14:46,370
My guess wasn't that spot on...

185
00:14:47,370 --> 00:14:49,330
This here's the entrance to the lab!

186
00:14:49,330 --> 00:14:50,950
Cool!

187
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:52,660
Flashy!

188
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:57,000
Before you enter, change into lab suits!

189
00:14:57,420 --> 00:15:00,210
That right there is a trancos, a changing room!

190
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,670
Welcome.

191
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:06,390
Please select your preferred attire.

192
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,550
My preferred attire...

193
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:16,480
What the hell is this?!

194
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:19,270
Try that lever on the dom shoes there.

195
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:20,940
They'll fit any old foot!

196
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:23,110
These, right?

197
00:15:23,690 --> 00:15:25,110
They look heavy...

198
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,160
So light!

199
00:15:29,660 --> 00:15:31,620
And cute!

200
00:15:31,620 --> 00:15:33,290
You look great in that, Robin!

201
00:15:33,290 --> 00:15:34,460
It's perfect!

202
00:15:34,460 --> 00:15:37,960
These could squeeze the life right out of you!

203
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,880
Why do you say morbid stuff like this...?

204
00:15:42,090 --> 00:15:44,300
These future outfits have me all hyped!

205
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:45,800
Way to go, Vegapunk!

206
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,640
They fit perfectly even on my body!

207
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:50,390
Super!

208
00:15:50,390 --> 00:15:53,140
Mine's just a regular aloha shirt!

209
00:15:54,350 --> 00:15:57,850
Well, Nami and Robin
look super cute, so who cares?!

210
00:15:57,850 --> 00:15:59,690
I've never seen fashion like this!

211
00:15:59,690 --> 00:16:01,820
Yours is great, Robin! You look tough!

212
00:16:01,820 --> 00:16:02,520
Yeah?

213
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:03,650
How do I look?

214
00:16:03,650 --> 00:16:05,490
You look like a perv in anything!

215
00:16:05,490 --> 00:16:07,070
You're too kind!

216
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:14,500
Geniuses can even see their own future...

217
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:16,960
What are you talking about, Vegapunk?

218
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:18,750
I think...

219
00:16:21,340 --> 00:16:23,050
I'm going to die soon.

220
00:16:23,050 --> 00:16:24,710
Enough with the jokes!

221
00:16:24,710 --> 00:16:26,300
That's not funny.

222
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:29,340
I just wanted you to know that...

223
00:16:29,970 --> 00:16:30,930
Dragon.

224
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:35,220
Shouldn't you have gone with them?

225
00:16:35,220 --> 00:16:36,980
This is a government island.

226
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:40,020
Who's gonna bust them out
if they get caught?

227
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:44,020
I thought that might be the case.

228
00:16:44,020 --> 00:16:45,650
Care for some tea?

229
00:16:45,650 --> 00:16:47,070
Sure. Thanks.

230
00:16:47,070 --> 00:16:49,240
My good sirs!

231
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:50,950
You're still here?

232
00:16:50,950 --> 00:16:53,160
N-Now wait just a minute!

233
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:58,790
I know I said I'd get off
anywhere that wasn't Wano...

234
00:16:58,790 --> 00:17:01,040
But not here, my good sirs!

235
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:02,880
This is a government island!

236
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:06,050
I heard you helped out our captain. Thanks.

237
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:06,920
Now scram.

238
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:11,050
I'll make them pay for this!

239
00:17:11,090 --> 00:17:14,760
At the Lab

240
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:19,430
That looks like fun!

241
00:17:19,430 --> 00:17:20,940
All right!

242
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,860
This is radical!

243
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,900
The stairs are moving!

244
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:30,780
They're coming right out of the ground!

245
00:17:34,030 --> 00:17:35,160
What's the mechanism?

246
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,660
What powers it?

247
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:39,120
Fire's what runs this island!

248
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:42,170
You can convert fire into any form of energy.

249
00:17:42,170 --> 00:17:44,000
Are there a lot of resources here?

250
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:47,460
I've been researching what things burn best.

251
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:53,390
If there was only a flame that wouldn't
go out, I could even make a sun!

252
00:17:53,390 --> 00:17:54,720
A sun?!

253
00:18:00,060 --> 00:18:00,890
Huh?!

254
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:02,350
That's a wall!

255
00:18:06,270 --> 00:18:07,440
Hey, open up!

256
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:09,400
What's the holdup? Come on through!

257
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,110
Don't let your peepers trick you.

258
00:18:12,740 --> 00:18:14,320
Lilith! Lilith!

259
00:18:14,820 --> 00:18:16,070
What's wrong, Edison?

260
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:21,040
Lilith, my sweet!

261
00:18:24,580 --> 00:18:26,590
I can't hear anything now–

262
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,760
His neck! His head!

263
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:30,960
Don't worry.

264
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:34,260
If his head were cut off,
there'd be blood everywhere.

265
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:37,010
Thanks for the commentary!
It wasn't scary at all!

266
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:39,770
Sanji! Are you alright?!

267
00:18:39,770 --> 00:18:40,600
Yeah.

268
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,520
You can just walk through.

269
00:18:42,520 --> 00:18:44,350
Doesn't look like it...

270
00:18:44,350 --> 00:18:45,230
Alright.

271
00:18:45,230 --> 00:18:46,360
What?!

272
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:47,110
I'll go, too.

273
00:18:47,110 --> 00:18:48,360
H-Hey...

274
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:49,480
Excuse me.

275
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,940
I went through...

276
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:53,950
Why?

277
00:19:01,330 --> 00:19:03,910
Why did they make it so confusing?

278
00:19:03,910 --> 00:19:04,830
Huh?

279
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:10,050
What?! The door's just iron on this side!

280
00:19:10,050 --> 00:19:11,800
How does it work?!

281
00:19:12,670 --> 00:19:14,010
Lilith's gone!

282
00:19:14,380 --> 00:19:15,630
Hey!

283
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:16,890
Walk right on ahead!

284
00:19:16,890 --> 00:19:18,600
Huh? Who's that?

285
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,720
My name's Vegapunk Edison!

286
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:22,640
Glad you could join us.

287
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:24,640
Step right this way!

288
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:30,570
Just a little more.

289
00:19:30,570 --> 00:19:32,780
I wonder what's ahead.

290
00:19:33,860 --> 00:19:35,990
Time to look for the treasure of the future!

291
00:19:35,990 --> 00:19:37,740
What's "the treasure of the future"?

292
00:19:37,740 --> 00:19:40,490
Something like flowers made of gemstones!

293
00:19:40,490 --> 00:19:43,250
I can't tell if that's childish or old-fashioned...

294
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:45,250
Future Kick!

295
00:20:00,430 --> 00:20:01,510
Someone's there!

296
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:04,350
Huh?

297
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:05,930
Hey! Why?!

298
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:08,150
Jinbe?!

299
00:20:08,150 --> 00:20:10,230
He's too young.

300
00:20:10,860 --> 00:20:12,610
He looks different, as well.

301
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:20,660
Possibility one: It's Jinbe's child!

302
00:20:22,030 --> 00:20:25,250
Possibility two: Jinbe was turned into a child!

303
00:20:25,620 --> 00:20:26,750
No...

304
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:29,210
Possibility three: He's Jinbe's doppelganger!

305
00:20:29,830 --> 00:20:31,170
He has wings...

306
00:20:31,170 --> 00:20:33,210
and a weird vibe...

307
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:36,010
Hey! Who are you?!

308
00:20:39,550 --> 00:20:43,810
He looks like a kid, but he's as big as Jinbe!

309
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:45,720
I've got a bad feeling about this...

310
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:48,770
Possibility four!

311
00:20:48,770 --> 00:20:50,730
It's a pacifista!

312
00:21:14,090 --> 00:21:15,960
It was a set-up!

313
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:18,670
I knew the government
wouldn't be so hospitable!

314
00:21:18,670 --> 00:21:20,090
Stop, Jinbe!

315
00:21:22,550 --> 00:21:25,930
He's not reacting to that name.

316
00:21:25,930 --> 00:21:28,730
So he's a clone of Jinbe?

317
00:21:33,650 --> 00:21:35,900
That doesn't make it easier!

318
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:38,280
And I'm not about to start beating up a kid!

319
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:47,950
He's a power user?!

320
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:51,670
What's going on?!

321
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,250
What do you wanna do, Nami?!
Do you wanna fight?!

322
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:57,210
Wait, Zeus!

323
00:21:59,630 --> 00:22:01,720
Hey! Hold on a sec!

324
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:03,220
That power belongs to...

325
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:12,390
Nami!

326
00:22:18,820 --> 00:22:20,320
Hey! Stop!

327
00:22:23,490 --> 00:22:25,240
Jinbe...

328
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,530
You bastard! Let go of Nami!

329
00:22:27,530 --> 00:22:29,240
Damn you!

330
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:33,290
Vegapunk's work or not,
I'll make you pay!

331
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:35,750
Alright! Death penalty it is!

332
00:22:36,380 --> 00:22:38,670
Even if you are...

333
00:22:38,670 --> 00:22:40,960
the real Jinbe!

334
00:22:51,770 --> 00:22:53,390
I concur.

335
00:22:53,390 --> 00:22:55,650
What you just did is unforgivable!

336
00:22:55,650 --> 00:22:57,770
Gigante Fleur!

337
00:23:07,780 --> 00:23:09,780
Sea Serpent Snapdragon!

338
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:19,290
Spank!

339
00:23:26,590 --> 00:23:27,800
Get away, Robin!

340
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:33,100
He uses fishman karate, too?!

341
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:35,940
Lethal Green Star!

342
00:23:35,940 --> 00:23:38,150
Skull Bombgrass!

343
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:47,320
Even though I know it's not Jinbe,
it just doesn't feel right!

344
00:23:49,820 --> 00:23:51,160
Did it work?!

345
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:53,540
Yeah, I think so!

346
00:23:58,290 --> 00:23:59,040
He's gone!

347
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:01,040
He's gone?!

348
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:02,170
Why?!

349
00:24:02,170 --> 00:24:04,300
I hit him, didn't I?!

350
00:24:13,180 --> 00:24:14,430
Hey!

351
00:24:14,430 --> 00:24:16,060
Let go of me!

352
00:24:17,020 --> 00:24:17,890
Usopp!

353
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:19,690
Sanji, leave it to me!

354
00:24:21,270 --> 00:24:23,400
Usopp, don't move!

355
00:24:27,360 --> 00:24:30,530
Damn you! Let go of me!

356
00:24:30,530 --> 00:24:33,790
I said don't move!

357
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:37,330
That energy...

358
00:24:37,330 --> 00:24:38,750
What in tarnation...?

359
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:41,460
Radical...

360
00:24:41,460 --> 00:24:43,880
Dodge it, S-Shark!

361
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:45,760
Beam!

362
00:24:55,890 --> 00:24:57,480
He used a darn laser beam!

363
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:58,850
Who is this feller?!

364
00:24:58,850 --> 00:25:01,560
It packs one helluva punch, too!

365
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:03,190
That was a close one!

